  <m>\eval{\dfdx{h}{t}}{t}{0}</m>,
</p>
</li>
<li>
<title>Acceleration</title>
<p>
<m>\eval{\dfdxn{h}{t}{2}}{t}{0}</m>
</p>
</li>
</dl>
Remember to go through the two step process of
differentiating and then dividing by <m>\dx{t}.</m> We insist.  
</p>
</statement>
</task>
<task>
