<task>
  <statement>
    <p>
      In  general the height of an object falling near the surface of
      the earth is given by
      <me>
        h(t)=h_0+v_0t-4.9t^2</me> meters.
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p>
              Show that the initial height is <m>h_0</m>, the initial velocity
              is <m>v_0</m>, and the acceleration is <m>=-9.8</m>.
</p>
</li>
<li>
  <p>
    For simplicity, assume <m>h_0=0</m>.  How high will the ball go?
</p>
