<p>

  <xref ref="PROBLEMsnell1">Problem\</xref> demonstrates that you have alternatives
  when solve any problem.  Consciously try to avoid getting locked in to
  a single solution scheme.  One alternative is to try to determine a
  single function of a single variable before differentiating.  At the
  other extreme we can just assign variable names to all of the
  important quantities in our problem and differentiate the equations
  relating these variables.
</p>
<p>

  The best approach will depend upon the problem. In fact, most of the
  time you'll find yourself using a mixture of the two. Keep in mind
  that it is always good to have alternatives.
</p>

