<section xml:id="sec:self-inters-curv">
<title>Self-intersecting Curves and Parametric Equations</title>
<introduction>
  <p>
    <!-- \label{sec:self-inters-curv} -->
    In <xref ref="PROBLEMClassicalCurves1">Problem~\</xref> we asked  you to find the line
    tangent to several interesting curves.  However, we were careful to ask
    only about relatively simple curves. In particular, none of the curves
    in <xref ref="PROBLEMClassicalCurves1">Problem~\</xref> intersected themselves. We
    avoided self-intersecting curves earlier because we didn't have the
    techniques necessary to address the problem of tangent lines at points
    where a curve crosses itself. We do now.

    But we need to broaden our thinking a bit.
</p>


