<problem xml:id="problem:FoliumOfDescartes1">
  <introduction>
    <p>
      <!-- \label{problem:FoliumOfDescartes1} -->
      Recall that the Folium of Descartes, <m>x^3+y^3=3xy</m>,  crosses itself at the origin.
</p>
</introduction>
<task>
  <statement>
    <p>
      Show that if <m> x(t)=\frac{3t}{1+t^3}</m> and
      <m> y(t)=\frac{3t^2}{1+t^3}</m> then <m>x</m> and <m>y</m> satisfy the equation
      of the Folium.
    </p>
  </statement>
</task>
<task>
  <statement>
    <p>
      Compute the fluxions of <m>x</m> and <m>y</m>.
    </p>
  </statement>
</task>
<task>
